  "text": "In [CITATION_1] the authors provide numerical evidence that RP-MBADMM suffers from slow convergence to a high precision level on L ∞ -norm of equality constraints. They also show that there is a benefit of utilizing RP-MBADMM solver mode -because the block structure is fixed, the solver needs to create a sub-problem matrix only once (it can also pre-factorize the matrices once to further reduce the computational burden) and store information for use when solving sub-problems in consequent iterations. In contrast, RAC-MBADMM mode reformulates sub-blocks for each iteration, meaning that the sub-problem matrices H σ i ,σ i + βA",
